						               													<description>This supplement marks an improvent in the &amp;quot;Triumph &amp;amp; Tragedy&amp;quot; game line. First of all the layout and the publishing quality is full-color and better by other points of view.&amp;#10;Many extended historical backgrounds is give with lot of details and accuracy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ALso, the supplement takes a more history-centred step, putting the very good T+T system away from the pulp/adventure genre that has been conceived for.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here we are infact in the colonial period, so the action is set in late 19th century and not the '20s and '30s of the 20th century like the original game and first supplment &amp;quot;Libertad o Muerte&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A lot of special rules are given to provide players with some setting specific mechanics, a great load of army lists have been furnished about the British Empire, its enemies and allies to recreate battles in Africa and Asia, from Egypt, to South Africa to India!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It more than just an army list, it is a real expansion and a full companion book that really expands and takes the base game to an higer level!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
